these within a wider framework of the 'third way'. They find a complex picture. Although the exact shape of the new welfare state is difficult to detect, it is clear that there have been major changes in areas such as citizenship, the mixed economy of welfare, the centrality of work in an active welfare state, and the appearance of new elements such as joined up government at the centre and new partnerships of governance at the periphery. New Labour, new welfare state? provides topical information on the debate on the future of the welfare state and is essential reading for students and researchers in social policy, politics and sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aMixed economyzGreat Britain. 0aPublic welfarezGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aBurchardt, Tania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharman, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCressey, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDean, Hartley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHewitt, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHills, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamieson, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemp, Peter A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Desmond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauder, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuschamp, Yolande, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaton, Calum, econt